<DOC><DOCNO> AP890904-0041 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-04-89 0514EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--AirCollision     09-04 0174</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Air Collision,0178</SECOND><HEAD>Helicopter, Small Plane Collide</HEAD><DATELINE>HOUMA, La. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A helicopter collided with a small plane,killing three people and scattering debris over a rural subdivision,authorities said.   Two people in the helicopter and the pilot of the single-engineplane were killed in SUnday night's crash about a mile from theHouma-Terrebonne Airport, said police Capt. John Dixon.   Dixon said the helicopter crashed and burned in an intersectionjust outside Houma's southern limits and the plane crashed into atree, but there were no injuries on the ground.   The helicopter was leased by Acadian Ambulance Service fromPetroleum Helicopters Inc., which serves the offshore oil industry.The crew had just flown from the hospital for maintenance work ontheir regular helicopter and were returning in a backup aircraftwhen the collision occurred, said Acadian Ambulance spokesmanRichard Zuschlag.   ``There is no explanation for it. It was a mid-air collision.Nobody knows who was at fault,'' Zuschlag said.   National Transportation Safety Board investigators were expectedto investigate the crash today, he said.</TEXT></DOC>